Defendant Kaleb M Scherrer in court with attorney Katie B. Bricco.  Lucas Paul Bennewitz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Sentencing argument by Atty. Bennewitz and Atty. Bricco.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

36 months  Imprisonment (Credit - 0 days )  CONSECUTIVE TO RACINE COUNTY CASE 14CF1198
- 18 months   of Initial Confinement
- 18 months  of Extended Supervision

Term of Probation: 3 Years CONCURRENT TO CURRENT PROBATION

Conditions of Probation:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Perform  20 hours of community service each year of probation with the 20 hours in the last year be completed by 4-30-18;
- Within first 120 days obtain a valid driver's license;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge.

Costs: $268.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $250.00
(To be paid as a condition of probation at the rate of $50.00  per month commencing 12-1-15)

